article.headline: Chicago St. 94, Longwood 86
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- David Holston scored 32 points to lead Chicago State in a 94-86 win over Longwood on Monday night. John Cantrell added 27 points and Carl Montgomery notched a double-double, scoring 13 and grabbing 18 rebounds for the Cougars (10-8, 3-7). Holston went 6-for-15 from beyond the arc and dished out five assists. Kevin Swecker, who hit 7 of 9 from long range and tallied five steals, led the Lancers (7-10) with a career-high 25 points. Dana Smith added 13 points and Antwan Carter and Billy Robinson had 12 apiece. Chicago State, which was up 46-39 at the break, grabbed the lead midway through the first half and never trailed again. E.J. Dawson pulled Longwood within 90-86 with 37 seconds left, but Tawrence Walton's pair of free throws and Cantrell's late layup gave Chicago State its final margin.
